{
  "video_id": "EAmmUIEsN9A",
  "title": "School strike for climate - save the world by changing the rules | Greta Thunberg | TEDxStockholm",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Akinori Oyama Reviewer: Peter van de Ven"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 7266.0,
      "end_time": 10233.0,
      "text": "When I was about eight years old,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 10233.0,
      "end_time": 14475.0,
      "text": "I first heard about something called climate change or global warming."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 15544.0,
      "end_time": 20114.0,
      "text": "Apparently, that was something humans have created by our way of living."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 21147.0,
      "end_time": 24764.0,
      "text": "I was told to turn off the lights to save energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25130.0,
      "end_time": 28384.0,
      "text": "and to recycle paper to save resources."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30193.0,
      "end_time": 33400.0,
      "text": "I remember thinking that it was very strange"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33234.0,
      "end_time": 36944.0,
      "text": "that humans, who are an animal species among others,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36944.0,
      "end_time": 41123.0,
      "text": "could be capable of changing the Earth&#39;s climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 42150.0,
      "end_time": 45486.0,
      "text": "Because if we were, and if it was really happening,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 45761.0,
      "end_time": 48664.0,
      "text": "we wouldn&#39;t be talking about anything else."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 49645.0,
      "end_time": 53925.0,
      "text": "As soon as you&#39;d turn on the TV, everything would be about that."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 54433.0,
      "end_time": 57466.0,
      "text": "Headlines, radio, newspapers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 57774.0,
      "end_time": 60615.0,
      "text": "you would never read or hear about anything else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 61105.0,
      "end_time": 63644.0,
      "text": "as if there was a world war going on."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 64763.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67285.0,
      "text": "But no one ever talked about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 68550.0,
      "end_time": 74790.0,
      "text": "If burning fossil fuels was so bad that it threatened our very existence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 74574.0,
      "end_time": 77203.0,
      "text": "how could we just continue like before?"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 78188.0,
      "end_time": 80423.0,
      "text": "Why were there no restrictions?"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 80955.0,
      "end_time": 83245.0,
      "text": "Why wasn&#39;t it made illegal?"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 84846.0,
      "end_time": 87816.0,
      "text": "To me, that did not add up."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 88213.0,
      "end_time": 90222.0,
      "text": "It was too unreal."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 92326.0,
      "end_time": 94902.0,
      "text": "So when I was 11, I became ill."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 95175.0,
      "end_time": 96967.0,
      "text": "I fell into depression,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 97244.0,
      "end_time": 98538.0,
      "text": "I stopped talking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 98923.0,
      "end_time": 100412.0,
      "text": "and I stopped eating."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 101624.0,
      "end_time": 105413.0,
      "text": "In two months, I lost about 10 kilos of weight."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 106814.0,
      "end_time": 109933.0,
      "text": "Later on, I was diagnosed with Asperger syndrome,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 110244.0,
      "end_time": 113214.0,
      "text": "OCD and selective mutism."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 114114.0,
      "end_time": 117685.0,
      "text": "That basically means I only speak when I think it&#39;s necessary -"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 117685.0,
      "end_time": 119595.0,
      "text": "now is one of those moments."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 119595.0,
      "end_time": 123183.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 129833.0,
      "end_time": 132215.0,
      "text": "For those of us who are on the spectrum,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 132215.0,
      "end_time": 134782.0,
      "text": "almost everything is black or white."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 135489.0,
      "end_time": 137159.0,
      "text": "We aren&#39;t very good at lying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 137159.0,
      "end_time": 140523.0,
      "text": "and we usually don&#39;t enjoy participating in this social game"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 140523.0,
      "end_time": 143780.0,
      "text": "that the rest of you seem so fond of."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 143780.0,
      "end_time": 144348.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 144613.0,
      "end_time": 147676.0,
      "text": "I think in many ways that we autistic are the normal ones,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 147966.0,
      "end_time": 150293.0,
      "text": "and the rest of the people are pretty strange,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 150293.0,
      "end_time": 151486.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 151486.0,
      "end_time": 154434.0,
      "text": "especially when it comes to the sustainability crisis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 154725.0,
      "end_time": 158450.0,
      "text": "where everyone keeps saying climate change is an existential threat"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 158850.0,
      "end_time": 161610.0,
      "text": "and the most important issue of all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 161459.0,
      "end_time": 164700.0,
      "text": "and yet they just carry on like before."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 165556.0,
      "end_time": 167321.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t understand that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 167624.0,
      "end_time": 170123.0,
      "text": "because if the emissions have to stop,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 170372.0,
      "end_time": 172504.0,
      "text": "then we must stop the emissions."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 173119.0,
      "end_time": 174944.0,
      "text": "To me that is black or white."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 175623.0,
      "end_time": 178385.0,
      "text": "There are no gray areas when it comes to survival."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 178755.0,
      "end_time": 181706.0,
      "text": "Either we go on as a civilization or we don&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 182571.0,
      "end_time": 184864.0,
      "text": "We have to change."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 185941.0,
      "end_time": 189875.0,
      "text": "Rich countries like Sweden need to start reducing emissions"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 189875.0,
      "end_time": 193155.0,
      "text": "by at least 15 percent every year."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 194124.0,
      "end_time": 198430.0,
      "text": "And that is so that we can stay below a two-degree warming target."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 198746.0,
      "end_time": 202198.0,
      "text": "Yet, as the IPCC have recently demonstrated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 203175.0,
      "end_time": 206410.0,
      "text": "aiming instead for 1.5 degrees Celsius"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 206287.0,
      "end_time": 209227.0,
      "text": "would significantly reduce the climate impacts."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 209853.0,
      "end_time": 213723.0,
      "text": "But we can only imagine what that means for reducing emissions."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 214822.0,
      "end_time": 217525.0,
      "text": "You would think the media and every one of our leaders"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 217532.0,
      "end_time": 219532.0,
      "text": "would be talking about nothing else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 219822.0,
      "end_time": 222930.0,
      "text": "but they never even mention it."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 222929.0,
      "end_time": 224658.0,
      "text": "Nor does anyone ever mention"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 224664.0,
      "end_time": 227784.0,
      "text": "the greenhouse gases already locked in the system."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 228265.0,
      "end_time": 231400.0,
      "text": "Nor that air pollution is hiding a warming"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 231380.0,
      "end_time": 234530.0,
      "text": "so that when we stop burning fossil fuels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 234341.0,
      "end_time": 236542.0,
      "text": "we already have an extra level of warming"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 236789.0,
      "end_time": 241238.0,
      "text": "perhaps as high as 0.5 to 1.1 degrees Celsius."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 242997.0,
      "end_time": 245549.0,
      "text": "Furthermore does hardly anyone speak about the fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 245549.0,
      "end_time": 249101.0,
      "text": "that we are in the midst of the sixth mass extinction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 249690.0,
      "end_time": 254611.0,
      "text": "with up to 200 species going extinct every single day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 256103.0,
      "end_time": 259744.0,
      "text": "that the extinction rate today"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 259744.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263544.0,
      "text": "is between 1,000 and 10,000 times higher"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 263544.0,
      "end_time": 265772.0,
      "text": "than what is seen as normal."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 268441.0,
      "end_time": 273804.0,
      "text": "Nor does hardly anyone ever speak about the aspect of equity or climate justice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 274175.0,
      "end_time": 277152.0,
      "text": "clearly stated everywhere in the Paris Agreement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 277539.0,
      "end_time": 281774.0,
      "text": "which is absolutely necessary to make it work on a global scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 283411.0,
      "end_time": 285267.0,
      "text": "That means that rich countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 285267.0,
      "end_time": 289204.0,
      "text": "need to get down to zero emissions within 6 to 12 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 289990.0,
      "end_time": 292262.0,
      "text": "with today&#39;s emission speed."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 294115.0,
      "end_time": 296255.0,
      "text": "And that is so that people in poorer countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 296255.0,
      "end_time": 298915.0,
      "text": "can have a chance to heighten their standard of living"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 298915.0,
      "end_time": 302483.0,
      "text": "by building some of the infrastructure that we have already built,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 302788.0,
      "end_time": 305836.0,
      "text": "such as roads, schools, hospitals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 305836.0,
      "end_time": 308885.0,
      "text": "clean drinking water, electricity, and so on."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 309632.0,
      "end_time": 314224.0,
      "text": "Because how can we expect countries like India or Nigeria"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 314228.0,
      "end_time": 316105.0,
      "text": "to care about the climate crisis"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 316110.0,
      "end_time": 321115.0,
      "text": "if we who already have everything don&#39;t care even a second about it"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 321115.0,
      "end_time": 323973.0,
      "text": "or our actual commitments to the Paris Agreement?"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 326374.0,
      "end_time": 330452.0,
      "text": "So, why are we not reducing our emissions?"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 331536.0,
      "end_time": 334834.0,
      "text": "Why are they in fact still increasing?"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 335745.0,
      "end_time": 338956.0,
      "text": "Are we knowingly causing a mass extinction?"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 339663.0,
      "end_time": 341354.0,
      "text": "Are we evil?"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 343430.0,
      "end_time": 345224.0,
      "text": "No, of course not."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 345625.0,
      "end_time": 347254.0,
      "text": "People keep doing what they do"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 347254.0,
      "end_time": 349894.0,
      "text": "because the vast majority doesn&#39;t have a clue"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 349894.0,
      "end_time": 353647.0,
      "text": "about the actual consequences of our everyday life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 354399.0,
      "end_time": 357374.0,
      "text": "and they don&#39;t know that rapid change is required."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 358405.0,
      "end_time": 362371.0,
      "text": "We all think we know, and we all think everybody knows,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 362372.0,
      "end_time": 363945.0,
      "text": "but we don&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 364633.0,
      "end_time": 366263.0,
      "text": "Because how could we?"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 368399.0,
      "end_time": 370384.0,
      "text": "If there really was a crisis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 370621.0,
      "end_time": 373508.0,
      "text": "and if this crisis was caused by our emissions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 373925.0,
      "end_time": 376202.0,
      "text": "you would at least see some signs."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 376973.0,
      "end_time": 380843.0,
      "text": "Not just flooded cities, tens of thousands of dead people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 381910.0,
      "end_time": 385250.0,
      "text": "and whole nations leveled to piles of torn down buildings."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 385829.0,
      "end_time": 388109.0,
      "text": "You would see some restrictions."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 388541.0,
      "end_time": 390225.0,
      "text": "But no."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 390699.0,
      "end_time": 392495.0,
      "text": "And no one talks about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 394284.0,
      "end_time": 399957.0,
      "text": "There are no emergency meetings, no headlines, no breaking news."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 400584.0,
      "end_time": 403570.0,
      "text": "No one is acting as if we were in a crisis."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 404234.0,
      "end_time": 408540.0,
      "text": "Even most climate scientists or green politicians"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 408324.0,
      "end_time": 412550.0,
      "text": "keep on flying around the world, eating meat and dairy."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 416192.0,
      "end_time": 421982.0,
      "text": "If I live to be 100, I will be alive in the year 2103."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 423663.0,
      "end_time": 429106.0,
      "text": "When you think about the future today, you don&#39;t think beyond the year 2050."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 430103.0,
      "end_time": 434917.0,
      "text": "By then, I will, in the best case, not even have lived half of my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 436244.0,
      "end_time": 437894.0,
      "text": "What happens next?"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 439484.0,
      "end_time": 445515.0,
      "text": "The year 2078, I will celebrate my 75th birthday."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 446375.0,
      "end_time": 451385.0,
      "text": "If I have children or grandchildren, maybe they will spend that day with me."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 452607.0,
      "end_time": 454878.0,
      "text": "Maybe they will ask me about you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 455309.0,
      "end_time": 458818.0,
      "text": "the people who were around, back in 2018."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 460711.0,
      "end_time": 463193.0,
      "text": "Maybe they will ask why you didn&#39;t do anything"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 463755.0,
      "end_time": 466185.0,
      "text": "while there still was time to act."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 467815.0,
      "end_time": 472193.0,
      "text": "What we do or don&#39;t do right now will affect my entire life"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 472193.0,
      "end_time": 475395.0,
      "text": "and the lives of my children and grandchildren."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 475885.0,
      "end_time": 478480.0,
      "text": "What we do or don&#39;t do right now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 478487.0,
      "end_time": 482606.0,
      "text": "me and my generation can&#39;t undo in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 486940.0,
      "end_time": 488959.0,
      "text": "So when school started in August of this year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 488959.0,
      "end_time": 491519.0,
      "text": "I decided that this was enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 492800.0,
      "end_time": 495940.0,
      "text": "I set myself down on the ground outside the Swedish parliament."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 496435.0,
      "end_time": 498853.0,
      "text": "I school striked for the climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 500602.0,
      "end_time": 503679.0,
      "text": "Some people say that I should be in school instead."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 504194.0,
      "end_time": 507854.0,
      "text": "Some people say that I should study to become a climate scientist"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 507854.0,
      "end_time": 511149.0,
      "text": "so that I can \"solve the climate crisis.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 512793.0,
      "end_time": 515556.0,
      "text": "But the climate crisis has already been solved."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 516325.00000000006,
      "end_time": 519293.00000000006,
      "text": "We already have all the facts and solutions."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 519845.0,
      "end_time": 522743.0,
      "text": "All we have to do is to wake up and change."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 524250.0,
      "end_time": 528654.0,
      "text": "And why should I be studying for a future that soon will be no more"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 528764.0,
      "end_time": 532724.0,
      "text": "when no one is doing anything whatsoever to save that future?"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 533784.0,
      "end_time": 537204.0,
      "text": "And what is the point of learning facts in the school system"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 537868.0,
      "end_time": 539827.0,
      "text": "when the most important facts"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 539827.0,
      "end_time": 543274.0,
      "text": "given by the finest science of that same school system"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 543545.0,
      "end_time": 547554.0,
      "text": "clearly means nothing to our politicians and our society."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 549513.0,
      "end_time": 552573.0,
      "text": "Some people say that Sweden is just a small country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 552794.0,
      "end_time": 555424.0,
      "text": "and that it doesn&#39;t matter what we do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 555826.0,
      "end_time": 560104.0,
      "text": "but I think that if a few children can get headlines all over the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 560104.0,
      "end_time": 562571.0,
      "text": "just by not coming to school for a few weeks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 563200.0,
      "end_time": 566320.0,
      "text": "imagine what we could all do together if you wanted to."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 566330.0,
      "end_time": 569449.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 570425.0,
      "end_time": 573940.0,
      "text": "Now we&#39;re almost at the end of my talk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 575140.0,
      "end_time": 580305.0,
      "text": "and this is where people usually start talking about hope,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 580885.0,
      "end_time": 585337.0,
      "text": "solar panels, wind power, circular economy, and so on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 586305.0,
      "end_time": 588343.0,
      "text": "but I&#39;m not going to do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 588676.0,
      "end_time": 593244.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve had 30 years of pep-talking and selling positive ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 593837.0,
      "end_time": 596124.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;m sorry, but it doesn&#39;t work."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 596834.0,
      "end_time": 598441.0,
      "text": "Because if it would have,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 598446.0,
      "end_time": 600704.0,
      "text": "the emissions would have gone down by now."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 600704.0,
      "end_time": 602357.0,
      "text": "They haven&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 603397.0,
      "end_time": 605845.0,
      "text": "And yes, we do need hope,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 606505.0,
      "end_time": 608114.0,
      "text": "of course we do."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 608574.0,
      "end_time": 612394.0,
      "text": "But the one thing we need more than hope is action."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 612965.0,
      "end_time": 616108.0,
      "text": "Once we start to act, hope is everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 617645.0,
      "end_time": 619885.0,
      "text": "So instead of looking for hope,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 619885.0,
      "end_time": 621745.0,
      "text": "look for action."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 622435.0,
      "end_time": 626444.0,
      "text": "Then, and only then, hope will come."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 628486.0,
      "end_time": 634970.0,
      "text": "Today, we use 100 million barrels of oil every single day."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 635895.0,
      "end_time": 638146.0,
      "text": "There are no politics to change that."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 639730.0,
      "end_time": 641675.0,
      "text": "There are no rules to keep that oil in the ground."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 643283.0,
      "end_time": 646320.0,
      "text": "So we can&#39;t save the world by playing by the rules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 646915.0,
      "end_time": 649495.0,
      "text": "because the rules have to be changed."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 650124.0,
      "end_time": 652131.0,
      "text": "Everything needs to change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 652601.0,
      "end_time": 654465.0,
      "text": "and it has to start today."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 654934.0,
      "end_time": 656730.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 656730.0,
      "end_time": 659422.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}